               <p>EDWARD STOW. I am shopman to Alexander Purse, a <rs id="t18270531-58-viclabel289" type="occupation">pawnbroker</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270531-58-victim448 t18270531-58-viclabel289"></join>, of <placeName id="t18270531-58-crimeloc290">London-wall</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18270531-58-crimeloc290" type="placeName" value="London-wall"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18270531-58-crimeloc290" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270531-58-off287 t18270531-58-crimeloc290"></join>. On the 26th of April, between twelve and one o'clock, I was behind the counter, and saw the prisoner enter the shop - he lifted up a bar, and took off these three waistcoats; he ran out - I pursued - he threw them down. I caught him, without losing sight of him, and they were picked up.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I saw a boy with them under his arm - he dropped them; I followed him, and took one up- the gentleman stopped me.</p>
